<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06039k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06039k">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06039k"> 39(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prefer oral to lecture</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">quand on raconte un &eacute;v&eacute;nement &agrave; l&apos;enfant, il le voit; s&apos;il ne le voit pas, il ne comprend plus. Aussi <mark>pr&eacute;f&egrave;re-t-il la narration orale &agrave; la lecture</mark>, parce que souvent le livre renferme des tours de phrase auxquels il n&apos;est pas habitu&eacute; et des expressions trop recherch&eacute;es ou tout &agrave; fait nouvelles qui n&apos;&eacute;veillent en lui aucune image. <font color="green">[when an event is told to the child, he sees it; if he does not see it, he does not understand anymore. So he prefers oral narrative to reading, because often the book contains phrases that he is not accustomed to, and expressions that are too much sought after or quite new, that do not awaken any image in him.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 16 footnote 2</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01109i" href="c01all.htm#c01109i">VI.C.01:109(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
